## Technical Specifications

### Architecture

```
{{ project_name | snake_case }}/
├── {{ project_name | snake_case }}.py    # Entry point
├── src/
│   ├── commands/      # CLI commands
│   ├── core/          # Business logic
│   ├── utils/         # Helpers
│   └── config.py      # Configuration
└── tests/             # Tests
```

### Code Standards

- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Maximum line length: 88 characters
- Comprehensive docstrings with examples
- Type hints for all functions
- Proper exit codes (0=success, 1=error, 2=usage)

## Development Workflow

### Adding a Command

1. Create command file in `src/commands/`
2. Implement command logic in `src/core/`
3. Register command in main CLI group
4. {% if include_tests %}Write tests{% endif +%}
5. Update documentation
6. Update CHANGELOG.md

### Release Process

1. Update version number
2. Update CHANGELOG.md
3. {% if include_tests %}Run full test suite{% endif +%}
4. Build distribution
5. Tag release: `git tag v{{ project_version }}`
6. Publish

